IZE=1 COLOR=#6F6F6F>4/4/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#6F6F6F>12:05:35 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">4-4 patch </font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Well just looked at the patch message and some interesting news.  First most combine containers just got heavier. &lt;f&gt;  In general I think this hurts the average player.  However containers with items that are NOT a valid recipe will NO LONGER combine and be destroyed, so the risk to the average player is gone (as is the weight benefit) but for those working in tradeskills, it just got a LOT easier to work on trades and to find new recipes. &lt;YEAH !!&gt;  To offset the container added weight, tailored 10 slot backpacks now have an inreased weight redution (10%) I think, check the patch message.  So all in all, this looks like a good patch.<br>
<br>
Storgue<br>
